  id: Thigh_Bone_Femur_R
  partName: Thigh Bone Femur Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right femur is the largest and strongest bone of the canine hindlimb, extending
    from the hip joint to the stifle joint. It supports major weight-bearing functions
    and serves as an attachment site for powerful muscles controlling locomotion
    and posture.
  - The femur articulates with the pelvis proximally and the tibia and patella distally,
    enabling efficient movement during walking, running, and jumping. Its structure
    provides stability, leverage, and force transmission necessary for hindlimb propulsion.
